<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Leicester are willing to offer £20m for St Etienne's Wesley Fofana after being encouraged that the 19-year-old may be open to leaving.</p>

<p>AC Milan and Everton have also checked on Fofana who was outstanding last season but the Foxes are leading the race as they continue their search for defensive reinforcements.</p>

<p>Brendan Rodgers utilised midfielder Wilfried Ndidi at centre-back on Saturday. </p>

<p>Leicester are willing to pay £20m for St Etienne's Wesley Fofana following negotiations</p>

<p>The Foxes have been encouraged that the 19-year-old may be open to leaving</p>

<p>New signing Timothy Castagne will join up with the Leicester camp soon due to international duty, after he joined the Midlands club from Atalanta in a deal worth £22million.</p>

<p>Rodgers sealed the Belgian's signature following Ben Chilwell's £50million exit to Chelsea, as the 24-year-old penned a five-year deal with Leicester. </p>

<p>Elsewhere, Foxes midfielder Adrien Silva has interest from Sampdoria. </p>

<p>Timothy Castagne has penned a five-year deal with Leicester City in a £22million deal</p>
